text: William Henry Harrison (September 25, 1880 – July 18, 1955) was a Canadian politician. He served in the Legislative Assembly of New Brunswick as member of the Conservative party representing Saint John City from 1925 to 1935. ==References== Category:1880 births Category:1955 deaths Category:20th-century Canadian politicians Category:People from Saint John, New Brunswick Category:Progressive Conservative Party of New Brunswick MLAs
title: William Henry Harrison (Canadian politician)
